IENCY VARIANCE\":\"This quiz involves calculating the operational labour efficiency variance based on the standard and actual times for an operation and the standard rate of pay.\"", "\"NON-FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE INDICATORS\":Non-financial performance indicators are metrics used to assess various aspects of a company's performance that are not directly related to financial outcomes. These indicators encompass areas such as quality, customer satisfaction, employee engagement, and operational efficiency, which can lead to better long-term performance. They complement financial performance measures and help avoid excessive cost-cutting that may harm the business. Examples of non-financial performance indicators include customer satisfaction, employee turnover, operational efficiency, student transfer rates, late enrolments, exam pass rates, labor turnover, student complaints, and the average number of employees.", "\"QUIZ ON NON-FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE INDICATORS\":\"This quiz involves identifying appropriate non-financial performance indicators to monitor and improve the performance of a department within Smithson Co. The correct answers are A (Percentage of quotations found to contain errors when checked) and C (Actual staff employed as a percentage of the quota for the department).\"", "\"QUIZ ON EFFECT OF LONG-TERM LOAN ON FINANCIAL RATIOS\":\"This quiz involves understanding the impact of raising a long-term loan to finance the purchase of non-current assets on a company's current ratio and financial gearing. The correct answer is A (No effect on current ratio, Increase in financial gearing).\"", "\"QUIZ ON EFFECT OF REDUCING CLOSING INVENTORY\":\"This quiz involves understanding the impact of reducing the value of closing inventory on a company's current ratio and financial gearing. The correct answer is C (Decrease in current ratio, Increase in financial gearing).\"", "\"QUIZ ON RETURN ON CAPITAL EMPLOYED FOR GRIPPA CO\":\"This quiz involves calculating the return on capital employed (ROCE) for Grippa Co based on given net profit margin and asset turnover. The correct answer is C (33.8%).\"", "\"QUIZ ON INCENTIVE SCHEME FOR PRODUCT QUALITY\":\"This quiz involves identifying the most appropriate basis for an incentive scheme aimed at improving product quality at Yobo Co. The correct answer is C (Levels of rework).\"", "\"QUIZ ON MEASURE FOR IMPROVING CUSTOMER SATISFACTION\":\"This quiz involves identifying the most appropriate measure for an incentive scheme aimed at improving customer satisfaction at Cawlin Co. The correct answer is B (A decrease in the number of calls referred to a supervisor).\"", "\"QUIZ ON PERFORMANCE MEASURE FOR PRODUCT QUALITY\":\"This quiz involves identifying the most appropriate performance measure for an incentive scheme aimed at improving product quality at Lukers Co. The correct answer is C (Volume of products returned by customers).\"", "\"FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE INDICATORS\":", "\"STAFF COST OF EACH SURGICAL PROCEDURE\":\"Staff cost of each surgical procedure is a measure of economy, assessing whether resources are acquired at the required quality for the lowest price.\"", "\"BALANCED SCORECARD STATEMENTS\":\"The quiz on Balanced Scorecard statements involves determining the truth of statements regarding the focus of the balanced scorecard on non-financial performance measures and internal and external matters concerning the organization.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}